  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Zephaniah when
        Josiah son of Amon was king of Judah. Zephaniah was the son of Cushi, son
        of Gedaliah, son of Amariah, son of Hezekiah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Coming Judgment against Judah
      content: "\u201CI will sweep away everything\n\tfrom the face of the earth,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will sweep away people and animals alike.\n\tI will sweep
        away the birds of the sky and the fish in the sea.\n\tI will reduce the wicked
        to heaps of rubble,[COMMENT[0]]and I will wipe humanity from the face of
        the earth,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will crush Judah and Jerusalem with my fist\n\tand destroy
        every last trace of their Baal worship.\n\tI will put an end to all the idolatrous
        priests,\n\tso that even the memory of them will disappear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they go up to their roofs\n\tand bow down to the sun, moon, and
        stars.\n\tThey claim to follow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tbut
        then they worship Molech,[COMMENT[0]] too.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Malcam, '
        - ft: 'a variant spelling of Molech; or it could possibly mean '
          body: their king.
    - title: 
      content: "And I will destroy those who used to worship me\n\tbut now no longer
        do.\n\tThey no longer ask for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        guidance\n\tor seek my blessings.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Stand in silence in the presence of the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tfor
        the awesome day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s judgment is
        near.\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has prepared his people for a great
        slaughter\n\tand has chosen their executioners.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: has prepared a sacrifice and sanctified his guests.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn that day of judgment,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201CI
        will punish the leaders and princes of Judah\n\tand all those following pagan
        customs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, I will punish those who participate in pagan worship ceremonies,\n\tand
        those who fill their masters\u2019 houses with violence and deceit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\t\u201Ca
        cry of alarm will come from the Fish Gate\n\tand echo throughout the New
        Quarter of the city.[COMMENT[0]]And a great crash will sound from the hills.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'the Second Quarter, '
        - ft: 'a newer section of Jerusalem. Hebrew reads '
          body: the Mishneh.
    - title: 
      content: 'Wail in sorrow, all you who live in the market area,[COMMENT[0]]for
        all the merchants and traders will be destroyed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'in the valley, '
        - ft: 'a lower section of Jerusalem. Hebrew reads '
          body: the Maktesh.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will search with lanterns in Jerusalem\u2019s darkest corners\n\tto
        punish those who sit complacent in their sins.\n\tThey think the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will do nothing to them,\n\teither good or bad.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So their property will be plundered,\n\ttheir homes will be ransacked.\n\tThey
        will build new homes\n\tbut never live in them.\n\tThey will plant vineyards\n\tbut
        never drink wine from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThat terrible day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is near.\n\tSwiftly
        it comes\u2014\n\ta day of bitter tears,\n\ta day when even strong men will
        cry out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It will be a day when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        anger is poured out\u2014\n\ta day of terrible distress and anguish,\n\ta
        day of ruin and desolation,\n\ta day of darkness and gloom,\n\ta day of clouds
        and blackness,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a day of trumpet calls and battle cries.\n\tDown go the walled cities\n\tand
        the strongest battlements!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBecause you have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\tI
        will make you grope around like the blind.\n\tYour blood will be poured into
        the dust,\n\tand your bodies will lie rotting on the ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your silver and gold will not save you\n\ton that day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        anger.\n\tFor the whole land will be devoured\n\tby the fire of his jealousy.\n\tHe
        will make a terrifying end\n\tof all the people on earth.[COMMENT[0]]"
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the people living in the land.
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: "Gather together\u2014yes, gather together,\n\tyou shameless nation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gather before judgment begins,\n\tbefore your time to repent is blown
        away like chaff.\n\tAct now, before the fierce fury of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        falls\n\tand the terrible day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        anger begins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, all who are humble,\n\tand
        follow his commands.\n\tSeek to do what is right\n\tand to live humbly.\n\tPerhaps
        even yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will protect you\u2014\n\tprotect
        you from his anger on that day of destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Judgment against Philistia
      content: "Gaza and Ashkelon will be abandoned,\n\tAshdod and Ekron torn down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And what sorrow awaits you Philistines[COMMENT[0]]who live along
        the coast and in the land of Canaan,\n\tfor this judgment is against you,
        too!\n\tThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will destroy you\n\tuntil not one
        of you is left.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Kerethites.
    - title: 
      content: "The Philistine coast will become a wilderness pasture,\n\ta place
        of shepherd camps\n\tand enclosures for sheep and goats.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The remnant of the tribe of Judah will pasture there.\n\tThey will
        rest at night in the abandoned houses in Ashkelon.\n\tFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God will visit his people in kindness\n\tand restore their prosperity
        again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Judgment against Moab and Ammon
      content: "\u201CI have heard the taunts of the Moabites\n\tand the insults
        of the Ammonites,\n\tmocking my people\n\tand invading their borders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now, as surely as I live,\u201D\n\tsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel,\n\t\u201CMoab and Ammon will
        be destroyed\u2014\n\tdestroyed as completely as Sodom and Gomorrah.\n\tTheir
        land will become a place of stinging nettles,\n\tsalt pits, and eternal desolation.\n\tThe
        remnant of my people will plunder them\n\tand take their land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will receive the wages of their pride,\n\tfor they have scoffed
        at the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will terrify them\n\tas he destroys
        all the gods in the land.\n\tThen nations around the world will worship the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\n\teach in their own land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Judgment against Ethiopia and Assyria
      content: "\u201CYou Ethiopians[COMMENT[0]] will also be slaughtered\n\tby my
        sword,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Cushites.
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike the lands of the
        north with his fist,\n\tdestroying the land of Assyria.\n\tHe will make its
        great capital, Nineveh, a desolate wasteland,\n\tparched like a desert.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The proud city will become a pasture for flocks and herds,\n\tand
        all sorts of wild animals will settle there.\n\tThe desert owl and screech
        owl will roost on its ruined columns,\n\ttheir calls echoing through the
        gaping windows.\n\tRubble will block all the doorways,\n\tand the cedar paneling
        will be exposed to the weather.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is the boisterous city,\n\tonce so secure.\n\t\u201CI am the
        greatest!\u201D it boasted.\n\t\u201CNo other city can compare with me!\u201D\n\tBut
        now, look how it has become an utter ruin,\n\ta haven for wild animals.\n\tEveryone
        passing by will laugh in derision\n\tand shake a defiant fist."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Rebellion and Redemption"
      content: "What sorrow awaits rebellious, polluted Jerusalem,\n\tthe city of
        violence and crime!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one can tell it anything;\n\tit refuses all correction.\n\tIt
        does not trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\tor draw near to its
        God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Its leaders are like roaring lions\n\thunting for their victims.\n\tIts
        judges are like ravenous wolves at evening time,\n\twho by dawn have left
        no trace of their prey.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Its prophets are arrogant liars seeking their own gain.\n\tIts priests
        defile the Temple by disobeying God\u2019s instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is still there in the city,\n\tand
        he does no wrong.\n\tDay by day he hands down justice,\n\tand he does not
        fail.\n\tBut the wicked know no shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have wiped out many nations,\n\tdevastating their fortress
        walls and towers.\n\tTheir streets are now deserted;\n\ttheir cities lie
        in silent ruin.\n\tThere are no survivors\u2014\n\tnone at all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I thought, \u2018Surely they will have reverence for me now!\n\tSurely
        they will listen to my warnings.\n\tThen I won\u2019t need to strike again,\n\tdestroying
        their homes.\u2019\n\tBut no, they get up early\n\tto continue their evil
        deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, be patient,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\t\u201CSoon
        I will stand and accuse these evil nations.\n\tFor I have decided to gather
        the kingdoms of the earth\n\tand pour out my fiercest anger and fury on them.\n\tAll
        the earth will be devoured\n\tby the fire of my jealousy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen I will purify the speech of all people,\n\tso that everyone
        can worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My scattered people who live beyond the rivers of Ethiopia[COMMENT[0]]will
        come to present their offerings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Cush.
    - title: 
      content: "On that day you will no longer need to be ashamed,\n\tfor you will
        no longer be rebels against me.\n\tI will remove all proud and arrogant people
        from among you.\n\tThere will be no more haughtiness on my holy mountain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who are left will be the lowly and humble,\n\tfor it is they
        who trust in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The remnant of Israel will do no wrong;\n\tthey will never tell lies
        or deceive one another.\n\tThey will eat and sleep in safety,\n\tand no one
        will make them afraid.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sing, O daughter of Zion;\n\tshout aloud, O Israel!\n\tBe glad and
        rejoice with all your heart,\n\tO daughter of Jerusalem!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will remove his hand of judgment\n\tand
        will disperse the armies of your enemy.\n\tAnd the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>\n\thimself,
        the King of Israel,\n\twill live among you!\n\tAt last your troubles will
        be over,\n\tand you will never again fear disaster.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On that day the announcement to Jerusalem will be,\n\t\u201CCheer
        up, Zion! Don\u2019t be afraid!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is living among you.\n\tHe
        is a mighty savior.\n\tHe will take delight in you with gladness.\n\tWith
        his love, he will calm all your fears.[COMMENT[0]]He will rejoice over you
        with joyful songs.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'He will be silent in his love. '
        - ft: 'Greek and Syriac versions read '
          body: He will renew you with his love.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will gather you who mourn for the appointed festivals;\n\tyou
        will be disgraced no more.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: The meaning of the Hebrew for this verse is uncertain.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "And I will deal severely with all who have oppressed you.\n\tI will
        save the weak and helpless ones;\n\tI will bring together\n\tthose who were
        chased away.\n\tI will give glory and fame to my former exiles,\n\twherever
        they have been mocked and shamed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On that day I will gather you together\n\tand bring you home again.\n\tI
        will give you a good name, a name of distinction,\n\tamong all the nations
        of the earth,\n\tas I restore your fortunes before their very eyes.\n\tI,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
